### Create a New User [POST]

You may create a new user using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing user information like firstname,lastname, email, password, company .

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "firstName": "Ben",
            "lastName": "Haggerthy",
            "email": "Haggerthy@mail.com",
            "password": "**********",
            "company": "Veritech"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: api.factory.zone/v1/users

    + Body

            {
                "userId": "30jhgghlkkjhfsdfuujkk",
                "userAccess": "employee",
                "firstName": "Ben",
                "lastName":"Haggerthy",
                "email":"Haggerthy@mail.com",
                "company": "Veritech",
                "createdAt": "2015-08-05T08:40:51.620Z"
            }

##User [/api.factory.zone/v1/users/{userId}]

+ Parameters

    + userId (number) - user id of type UUID

### Retrieve User [GET]

This retrieves information partaining to a single user of known id

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "userId": "hh465jkkvk78fuystfmkknxn",
            "userAccess": "employee",
            "firstName": "Mark",
            "lastName":"Guttenberg",
            "email":"guttenberg@mail.com",
            "company": "Veritech",
            "createdAt": "2015-08-05T08:40:51.620Z"
        }

### Edit User [PUT]

You can modify user information with this

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "email": "chris@mail.com",
        }

+ Response 204 (No content)


### Remove User [DELETE]

You can remove a user 

+ Response 204 (No Content)
    

